description.narrative: By 2025, Ministries of Health and partners have strengthened capacity to plan, deliver, monitor and report on quality maternal, neonatal, child and adolescent health and HIV services., which contributes to Adolescent Health And Nutrition, Child Health, Child Health (Covid), Hiv Prevention, Maternal And Newborn Health, Treatment And Care Of Children Living With Hiv. UNICEF aims to achieve this through Evaluations, Research And Data, Systems Strengthening And Institution Building. This contributes to the following Country Programme result: By 2025, more neonates, infants and children survive and thrive, and fewer women die during pregnancy and childbirth.
